  "text": "C. Western analysis of HIF-1alpha U2OS cells (a human osteosarcoma cell line) were plated at 80-90% confluency in a 6-well plate and exposed to hypoxia and normoxia using the hypoxic insert device. The cell-seeded plate was placed in the incubator and the device was nested and exposed to either 0.5% oxygen (hypoxia), 21% oxygen, or 10 µM CoCl 2 as a control. CoCl 2 has been previously shown to mimic the hypoxic state and as a result cause induction of HIF-1µ [CITATION_1] . After 24 hours, cell lysates were immediately harvested using lysis buffer. Lysate protein was separated on an SDS-Page gel and HIF-1α was detected using the mouse monoclonal H1alpha67 antibody.",
